---
import DonationCard from "../../components/DonationCard.astro";
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import ZakatCalculator from "../../components/ZakatCalculator.astro";
---

<Layout>
  <style>
    .breadcrumb-bg::before {
      content: "";
      position: absolute;
      top: 0;
      left: 0;
      width: 100%;
      height: 100%;
      background-image: url("/assets/images/breadcrumb/zakat-bg.png");
      background-size: cover;
      background-repeat: no-repeat;
      background-position: 100% 100%;
      opacity: 1;
      -webkit-transition: opacity 0.3s ease;
      transition: opacity 0.3s ease;
      z-index: -1;
    }
  </style>
  <main>
    <!-- Breadcrumb Area S t a r t -->
    <section class="breadcrumb-section breadcrumb-bg">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="breadcrumb-text">
          <nav
            aria-label="breadcrumb"
            class="breadcrumb-nav wow fadeInUp"
            data-wow-delay="0.0s"
          >
            <ul class="breadcrumb listing">
              <li class="breadcrumb-item single-list">
                <a href="/" class="single">Home</a>
              </li>
              <li class="breadcrumb-item single-list" aria-current="page">
                <a href="/appeals" class="single">Appeals </a>
              </li>
              <li class="breadcrumb-item single-list" aria-current="page">
                <a href="/appeals/zakat" class="single">Zakat Calculator</a>
              </li>
            </ul>
          </nav>
          <h1 class="title wow fadeInUp" data-wow-delay="0.1s">
            Zakat Calculator
          </h1>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
    <!-- End-of Breadcrumb Area -->
    <DonationCard programId={[7, 14, 15]} />

    <div
      id="calculator"
      class="section-tittle mb-50 container"
      style="text-align: center;"
    >
      <h2 class="title font-700" style="color: #156E9D;">
        Simplify Your Zakat Calculation
      </h2>
      <p class="pera">
        Determining your Zakat seems to be a difficult task. However, it isn't
        as challenging as you might think of it. All you need to do is
        categorise your assets and liabilities in away that makes it convenient
        for you to calculate Zakat. To make it even more convenient and quick,
        use our Zakat Calculator to find out how much you need to pay.
        <br /><br />
        AWF Zakat Calculator has simplified the calculation by dividing assets into
        items to be considered to pay Zakat for (such as gold, silver, cash, savings,
        and business assets) and deductible liabilities (including debts and other
        outgoing payments). Using this breakdown, you can easily calculate Zakat.
        <br /><br />

        Once you assess the value of your net assets, you can determine the
        amount of Zakat. owed. It's crucial to compare your net assets to the
        nisab threshold to find out whether Zakat is obligatory.
      </p>
    </div>
    <ZakatCalculator />
    <section id="section-tittle">
      <div class="container mt-5">
        <div class="row justify-content-between align-items-center">
          <!-- Left Column: Text Content -->
          <div class="col-md-6 mb-4 align-self-center">
            <div class="nisab-div section-title mb-4">
              <h2 class="nisab-title">Nisab of Zakat</h2>
              <p class="nisab-description">
                The Nisab of Zakat is the minimum amount of wealth a Muslim
                possesses. These assets must be in the possession for over one
                lunar year to be eligible to pay Zakat. The sum is commonly
                known as the nisab threshold.
              </p>
              <p class="nisab-description">
                The nisab of Zakat is calculated on the values of Gold and
                Silver. In 2024, the determined value of nisab is 87.48 grams of
                gold and 612.36 grams of silver.
              </p>
            </div>
            <div class="nisab-div section-title mb-4">
              <h2 class="nisab-title-2">
                CURRENT NISAB VALUE <span style="color:#156e9d;"
                  >(11 November 2024)</span
                >
              </h2>
              <div class="nisab-cards">
                <div class="nisab-card">
                  <p>Gold Nisab*</p>
                  <h5>£5,848.69</h5>
                  <span>(87.48g)</span>
                </div>
                <div class="nisab-card">
                  <p>Silver Nisab*</p>
                  <h5>£478.45</h5>
                  <span>(612.36g)</span>
                </div>
              </div>
              <p class="nisab-note">*Nisab values are updated regularly</p>
              <p class="nisab-footer">
                Utilise our Zakat Calculator 2024 to determine how much you need
                to pay.
              </p>
            </div>
            <div class="calculate-btn-div">
              <a href="#calculator" class="btn-primary-fill">
                CALCULATE YOUR ZAKAT
              </a>
            </div>
          </div>
          <!-- Right Column: Image -->
          <div class="col-md-5 mb-4 mb-md-0">
            <img
              src="/assets/images/appeals/sadaqah-4.jpg"
              alt="Ramadan - The Blessed Month of Giving"
              class="img-fluid rounded"
            />
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="question-area section-padding">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="row">
          <div class="col my-auto">
            <!-- Section Tittle -->
            <div class="section-tittle mb-50" style="text-align: center;">
              <h2 class="title font-700">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
              <p class="pera">
                When deciding which charity to donate to, it's important to do
                your search and find one that aligns with your values and
                interests.
              </p>
            </div>
            <div class="accordion" id="accordionExample">
              <div class="accordion-item">
                <h2 class="accordion-header" id="headingOne">
                  <button
                    class="accordion-button"
                    type="button"
                    data-bs-toggle="collapse"
                    data-bs-target="#collapseOne"
                    aria-expanded="true"
                    aria-controls="collapseOne"
                    >How is the amount of Zakat calculated?
                  </button>
                </h2>
                <div
                  id="collapseOne"
                  class="accordion-collapse collapse show"
                  aria-labelledby="headingOne"
                  data-bs-parent="#accordionExample"
                >
                  <div class="accordion-body">
                    Zakat is typically calculated as 2.5% of one's savings and
                    wealth above the Nisab threshold. This includes cash, gold,
                    silver, and other assets held for more than a lunar year.
                    The Nisab is the minimum amount of wealth a Muslim must have
                    before they are obligated to pay Zakat, equivalent to 87.48
                    grams of gold or 612.36 grams of silver.
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="accordion-item">
                <h2 class="accordion-header" id="headingTwo">
                  <button
                    class="accordion-button collapsed additional-styles"
                    type="button"
                    data-bs-toggle="collapse"
                    data-bs-target="#collapseTwo"
                    aria-expanded="false"
                    aria-controls="collapseTwo"
                    >Can Zakat be given to family members?</button
                  >
                </h2>
                <div
                  id="collapseTwo"
                  class="accordion-collapse collapse"
                  aria-labelledby="headingTwo"
                  data-bs-parent="#accordionExample"
                >
                  <div class="accordion-body">
                    Zakat can be given to family members who qualify under the
                    categories of recipients, provided they are not immediate
                    dependents, such as one's parents, children, or spouse. It
                    is encouraged to help extended family members in need.
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="accordion-item">
                <h2 class="accordion-header" id="headingThree">
                  <button
                    class="accordion-button collapsed additional-styles"
                    type="button"
                    data-bs-toggle="collapse"
                    data-bs-target="#collapseThree"
                    aria-expanded="false"
                    aria-controls="collapseThree"
                    >When should Zakat be paid?</button
                  >
                </h2>
                <div
                  id="collapseThree"
                  class="accordion-collapse collapse"
                  aria-labelledby="headingThree"
                  data-bs-parent="#accordionExample"
                >
                  <div class="accordion-body">
                    Zakat is due once a lunar year (Hijri year) has passed since
                    the wealth reached the Nisab threshold. Many Muslims choose
                    to pay their Zakat during the month of Ramadan due to its
                    increased spiritual significance, but it can be paid at any
                    time of the year.
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="accordion-item">
                <h2 class="accordion-header" id="headingFour">
                  <button
                    class="accordion-button collapsed additional-styles"
                    type="button"
                    data-bs-toggle="collapse"
                    data-bs-target="#collapseFour"
                    aria-expanded="false"
                    aria-controls="collapseFour"
                    >How can one ensure their Zakat reaches the eligible
                    recipients?</button
                  >
                </h2>
                <div
                  id="collapseFour"
                  class="accordion-collapse collapse"
                  aria-labelledby="headingFour"
                  data-bs-parent="#accordionExample"
                >
                  <div class="accordion-body">
                    It is important to choose reputable and trustworthy
                    organizations or individuals who have a clear understanding
                    of Zakat distribution rules. Many Islamic charitable
                    organizations specialize in distributing Zakat according to
                    Islamic guidelines. Verifying their processes and
                    transparency can help ensure that Zakat reaches those in
                    need.
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
  <style>
    /* General Styles */
    body {
      font-family: "Arial", sans-serif;
      margin: 0;
      padding: 0;
      background-color: #f9f9f9;
    }

    .section-padding {
      padding: 40px 0;
    }

    .container {
      max-width: 1200px;
      margin: auto;
    }

    /* Title and Description */
    .nisab-title {
      align-items: center;
      justify-content: center;
      font-size: 1.8rem;
      color: #156e9d;
      font-weight: 700;
      margin-bottom: 10px;
    }

    .nisab-title-2 {
      align-items: center;
      justify-content: center;
      font-size: 1rem;
      color: black;
      font-weight: 200;
      margin-bottom: 10px;
    }

    .nisab-div {
      text-align: center;
    }

    .nisab-description {
      font-size: 1rem;
      color: #666666;
      line-height: 1.5;
      margin-bottom: 20px;
    }

    .nisab-subtitle {
      font-size: 1.2rem;
      font-weight: 700;
      color: #333333;
      margin-bottom: 10px;
      align-items: center;
      justify-content: center;
    }

    /* Nisab Cards */
    .nisab-cards {
      display: flex;
      margin-bottom: 20px;
    }

    .nisab-card {
      flex: 1;
      text-align: center;
      padding: 15px;
      border: 1px solid #156e9d;
      background-color: #f9f9f9;
    }

    .nisab-card p {
      font-size: 1rem;
      color: #333333;
      margin-bottom: 5px;
    }

    .nisab-card h5 {
      font-size: 1.4rem;
      color: #156e9d;
      margin: 0;
    }

    .nisab-card span {
      font-size: 0.9rem;
      color: #999999;
    }

    /* Notes and Button */
    .nisab-note {
      font-size: 1rem;
      color: #156e9d;
      margin-bottom: 15px;
    }

    .nisab-footer {
      font-size: 1rem;
      color: #333333;
      margin-bottom: 20px;
    }

    .btn-primary-fill {
      display: inline-block;
      padding: 12px 20px;
      font-size: 1rem;
      font-weight: 600;
      color: #ffffff;
      background-color: #156e9d;
      border: none;
      border-radius: 35px;
      text-decoration: none;
      text-align: center;
    }
    .calculate-btn-div {
      text-align: center;
      justify-content: center;
    }

    .btn-primary-fill:hover {
      background-color: #0f4d6d;
    }

    /* Image Styles */
    .img-fluid {
      max-width: 100%;
      height: auto;
      border-radius: 12px;
    }

    /* Responsive Design */
    @media (max-width: 768px) {
      .nisab-cards {
        flex-direction: column;
      }
    }
  </style>
</Layout>
